climbs.name: Story Pole
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, September 2001

content.description: An easy chimney to hand sized crack on this easy outing.
content.location: Far right side of the crag.

climbs.name: Pine Needles Galore
climbs.fa: Jeff Brennan and Pat Brennan, September 2001

content.description: Climb a left-facing corner to a ledge with pine needles and continue up the nice hand crack above while enjoying the prickly pine needles.
content.location:
Just right of

Broomstick

near the center of the crag.

climbs.name: Fish and Chips
climbs.fa: Eric Tipton and Kenn Kenaga, September 2001

content.description: Wander up the low angle face passing a thin crack and then more face climbing before a hand crack finish.
content.location:
Located between

Pine Needles Galore

and

Story Pole

.

climbs.name: Finish Work
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan,  Jeff Brennan, Kenn Kenaga and Eric Tipton, September 2001

content.description: Climb easy broken terrain to a ledge then continue up the face above via a hand crack on a slab - watch for lichen and pine needles!
content.location:
The next crack right of

Compared to What

.

climbs.name: Compared to What
climbs.fa: Kenn Kenaga, Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, September 2001

content.description: Scramble up blocky terrain to gain a hand crack that passes a distinct yellow patch of lichen.
content.location: Far left side of the crag.

climbs.name: Broomstick
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan and Jeff Brennan, September 2001

content.description: Easy climbing up blocky terrain gains a ledge at the base of a hand crack splitting the slab above.
content.location:
Between

Finish Work

and

Pine Needles Galore

.
